{
  "documentMetadata": {
    "title": "Histoplasmosis, Mediastinal",
    "lastUpdated": "2024-08-26",
    "sourceFile": "Histoplasmosis, Mediastinal.pdf"
  },
  "content": [
    {
      "type": "header",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Clinical Setting"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "items": [
        "These complications of histoplasmosis infection are due to an exuberant immune response to the infection and not associated with a high burden of organisms. Patients are often culture and antigen negative.",
        "Mediastinal lymphadenitis often presents as chest pain, dysphagia and/or cough due to bronchial or esophageal compression.",
        "Mediastinal granulomas are often asymptomatic but may present with compressive symptoms.",
        "Mediastinal fibrosis may present as occlusion of airways or vessels."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "header",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Etiologies"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "items": [
        "Histoplasma capsulatum"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "header",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Primary Regimens"
    },
    {
      "type": "nestedContent",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "header",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Mediastinal lymphadenitis:"
        },
        {
          "type": "list",
          "items": [
            "Asymptomatic or mild symptoms < 1 month: no treatment"
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "drugRegimen",
          "regimenData": {
            "appliesTo": {
              "description": "Mild symptoms > 1 month"
            },
            "components": [
              {
                "drug": "Itraconazole",
                "dose": "200 mg",
                "frequency": "tid for 3 days then bid"
              }
            ],
            "durationDetail": {
              "fixedDuration": "6-12 weeks"
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "drugRegimen",
          "regimenData": {
            "appliesTo": {
              "description": "Severe cases with obstruction or compression of vital structures"
            },
            "components": [
              {
                "drug": "Itraconazole",
                "notes": "(dosing and duration as above)"
              },
              {
                "drug": "Prednisone",
                "dose": "0.5-1 mg/kg/day",
                "connector": "+"
              }
            ],
            "durationDetail": {
              "fixedDuration": "tapered over 1-2 weeks"
            }
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "nestedContent",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "header",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Mediastinal granuloma:"
        },
        {
          "type": "list",
          "items": [
            "Asymptomatic: no treatment"
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "drugRegimen",
          "regimenData": {
            "appliesTo": {
              "description": "Symptomatic"
            },
            "components": [
              {
                "drug": "Itraconazole",
                "notes": "(dosing and duration as above)"
              }
            ]
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "nestedContent",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "header",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Mediastinal fibrosis:"
        },
        {
          "type": "list",
          "items": [
            "Many experts believe that neither antifungal therapy nor steroids are helpful",
            "Consider stenting of affected structures (Medicine (Baltimore) 90:412, 2011)"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "header",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Alternative Regimens"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "items": [
        "If itraconazole is not an option for the patient as above, may consider Posaconazole"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "header",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Comments"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "items": [
        "IDSA treatment guidelines: Clin Infect Dis 45:807, 2007."
      ]
    }
  ]
}
